<section xml:id="sec-decimals" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Decimals</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
        Murunga a grade <m>7</m> student carries a bag weighing <m>450 g</m>. He can convert the mass of his bag to kg i.e <m>\frac{450 g}{1000 g} \times 1 kg  = 0.45 kg</m>. Murunga used decimals to identify the mass of his bag in kg.
        </p>
        <exploration>
            <statement>
                <p>
               An example of a decimal number is <m> 3.75</m>. The whole number part is 3,the decimal part is 0.75 which represents 75 hundredths.
                </p>
            </statement>
        </exploration>
    </introduction>
